{#- ═══ SELECTOR ISLAND — full-width section; the .calc widget markup is preserved
    VERBATIM (the selector JS binds to data-calc / data-select-formula / data-calc-sel /
    data-out — class restyle on the result CTA is behavior-safe). id="calc" kept so the
    hero "Skip to the calculator" anchor still lands. ═══ -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="calc">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">The selector</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="max-width:24ch;margin-bottom:10px;">Find the plan that fits.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 28px;max-width:66ch;">Pick the option that fits in each row. The recommendation updates as you go &mdash; and it&rsquo;s based on features, never on price.</p>

    <div class="calc" data-calc data-select-formula="planselect">
      <form class="calc__form" aria-describedby="calc-disclaimer-top">
        <p class="calc__formnote" id="calc-disclaimer-top">Recommends on feature fit &mdash; Intuit sets pricing, check Intuit.</p>
        <div class="calc__field intake-field">
          <label class="intake-field__label" for="sel-users">How many people need access?</label>
          <select id="sel-users" data-calc-sel="users">
            <option value="1">Just me</option>
            <option value="3">2&ndash;3 people</option>
            <option value="5">4&ndash;5 people</option>
            <option value="25">6&ndash;25 people</option>
            <option value="40">More than 25</option>
          </select>
        </div>
        <div class="calc__field intake-field">
          <label class="intake-field__label" for="sel-inventory">Do you track product inventory?</label>
          <select id="sel-inventory" data-calc-sel="inventory">
            <option value="0">No</option>
            <option value="1">Yes &mdash; track inventory quantities &amp; cost</option>
          </select>
        </div>
        <div class="calc__field intake-field">
          <label class="intake-field__label" for="sel-projects">Do you need project or job profitability?</label>
          <select id="sel-projects" data-calc-sel="projects">
            <option value="0">No</option>
            <option value="1">Yes &mdash; profitability by project/job</option>
          </select>
        </div>
        <div class="calc__field intake-field">
          <label class="intake-field__label" for="sel-classes">Track by class, department, or location?</label>
          <select id="sel-classes" data-calc-sel="classes">
            <option value="0">No</option>
            <option value="1">Yes &mdash; class/location reporting</option>
          </select>
        </div>
        <div class="calc__field intake-field">
          <label class="intake-field__label" for="sel-billtime">Bill clients for tracked time?</label>
          <select id="sel-billtime" data-calc-sel="billtime">
            <option value="0">No</option>
            <option value="1">Yes &mdash; billable time on invoices</option>
          </select>
        </div>
      </form>

      <div class="calc__result" id="calc-result" role="status" aria-live="polite">
        <p class="calc__result-label">Recommended plan</p>
        <p class="calc__result-range calc__result-range--text"><span data-out="primary">&mdash;</span></p>
        <p class="calc__result-why" data-out="text">Answer the questions above to see which plan fits.</p>
        <p class="calc__result-disclaimer">A <strong>fit-based starting point</strong>, not a price comparison. Intuit sets and changes QuickBooks pricing &mdash; check current prices at Intuit. Plan features can change; a Certified ProAdvisor can confirm the right tier for your business.</p>
        <a class="btn btn-cta calc__result-cta" href="/contact/?intent=quickbooks-setup" data-ga="cta_click" data-tb-event="calc_to_quote" style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:9px;height:50px;padding:0 22px;border-radius:12px;font-size:15px;font-weight:600;">Book the discovery call</a>
      </div>

      <noscript>
        <div class="calc__noscript">
          <p>The live selector needs JavaScript. The short version: <strong>inventory, project profitability, or class tracking → Plus</strong>; <strong>more than five users → Advanced</strong>; <strong>multiple users without those features → Essentials</strong>; <strong>a single user with simple needs → Simple Start</strong>. The full comparison is below, or <a href="/contact/?intent=quickbooks-setup">book a free discovery call</a>.</p>
        </div>
      </noscript>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- ═══ THE DECIDING FEATURES — fit-not-price prose + the QBO plan matrix as a v2 .cmp
    table (data-col for mobile stacking). sand alt band. ═══ -#}
<section class="sec reveal hub-rt--alt" id="plan-select-how" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct read read--doc">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">The deciding features</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:14px;">What separates the QuickBooks Online plans.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 24px;max-width:66ch;">Features, not price &mdash; the capabilities that actually determine which tier you need. Pricing is set by Intuit; confirm current costs there.</p>
    <table class="cmp">
      <caption class="sr-only">Key feature differences across QuickBooks Online plans (features only, no pricing).</caption>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th scope="col">Capability</th>
          <th scope="col">Simple Start</th>
          <th scope="col">Essentials</th>
          <th scope="col">Plus</th>
          <th scope="col">Advanced</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><th scope="row" data-col="Capability">Users (billed seats)</th><td class="num" data-col="Simple Start">1</td><td class="num" data-col="Essentials">Up to 3</td><td class="num" data-col="Plus">Up to 5</td><td class="num" data-col="Advanced">Up to 25</td></tr>
        <tr><th scope="row" data-col="Capability">Bill management &amp; time tracking</th><td data-col="Simple Start">&ndash;</td><td data-col="Essentials">Yes</td><td data-col="Plus">Yes</td><td data-col="Advanced">Yes</td></tr>
        <tr><th scope="row" data-col="Capability">Inventory tracking</th><td data-col="Simple Start">&ndash;</td><td data-col="Essentials">&ndash;</td><td data-col="Plus">Yes</td><td data-col="Advanced">Yes</td></tr>
        <tr><th scope="row" data-col="Capability">Project / job profitability</th><td data-col="Simple Start">&ndash;</td><td data-col="Essentials">&ndash;</td><td data-col="Plus">Yes</td><td data-col="Advanced">Yes</td></tr>
        <tr><th scope="row" data-col="Capability">Class &amp; location tracking</th><td data-col="Simple Start">&ndash;</td><td data-col="Essentials">&ndash;</td><td data-col="Plus">Yes</td><td data-col="Advanced">Yes</td></tr>
        <tr><th scope="row" data-col="Capability">Custom roles, deeper reporting, automation</th><td data-col="Simple Start">&ndash;</td><td data-col="Essentials">&ndash;</td><td data-col="Plus">&ndash;</td><td data-col="Advanced">Yes</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <div class="prose" style="margin-top:24px;">
      <p>The logic is simple once you see it. <strong>Inventory, project profitability, or class/location tracking all require Plus</strong> &mdash; Simple Start and Essentials don&rsquo;t include them, so if you need any one of them, Plus is your floor. <strong>More than five users requires Advanced</strong>, which raises the seat limit to 25 and adds custom roles, batch tools, and deeper reporting. If you don&rsquo;t need those features, the smaller (and less expensive) plans are the honest choice &mdash; there&rsquo;s no benefit to paying for capabilities you won&rsquo;t use.</p>
      <p>Plan names, feature sets, and user limits are Intuit&rsquo;s and can change; this reflects the current QuickBooks Online lineup at a feature level. For exact, current pricing and any limited-time offers, go to Intuit directly &mdash; we deliberately don&rsquo;t republish Intuit&rsquo;s prices here. For a side-by-side capability matrix, see our <a href="/quickbooks/compare/online-plans/">QuickBooks Online plan comparison</a>; to talk it through, our <a href="/quickbooks/which-plan-is-right/">which-plan guide</a> goes deeper.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

